<subSubSection id="8D8D65142A5C2C7FB8E7C582FD85E07B" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8E7C582FD85E07B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8E7C582FED2E1DB" bold="true" box="[151,268,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="02974D1C2A5C2C7FB962C582FDDFE1DB" box="[274,513,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tosta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudospeculum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB962C582FDDFE1DB" box="[274,513,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Tosta pseudospeculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECD057F62A5C2C7FBA78C582FD83E1DB" box="[520,605,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" rank="species">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FBA78C582FD83E1DB" bold="true" box="[520,605,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles most 
<taxonomicName id="02974D1C2A5C2C7FBB60C582FBD3E1DB" authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[784,1037,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tosta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tosta">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FBB60C582FC5AE1DB" box="[784,900,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Tosta tosta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A1064B6E2A5C2C7FBBFAC582FBD3E1DB" author="Evans" box="[906,1037,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" refString="Evans, W. H. (1953) A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. (Groups E, F, G) Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History), London, 246 pp." type="book" year="1953">
Evans, 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBBA8C582FBD3E1DB" box="[984,1037,152,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by its wider wingspan, the darker upperside wings with bands less marked than in 
<taxonomicName id="02974D1C2A5C2C7FBBFFC5A2FC03E1BB" box="[911,989,184,207]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tosta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tosta">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FBBFFC5A2FC03E1BB" box="[911,989,184,207]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">T. tosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ampulla separate from harpe and highly modified in a process with the distal portion dilated and serrated, and lamella antevaginalis with two spine-like well sclerotized projections extending laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D8D65142A5C2C7FB8B7C402FB18E2FB" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="description">
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C402FC78E03B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C402FE8CE05B" bold="true" box="[199,338,280,303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB92CC402FE48E05B" box="[348,406,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Head</emphasis>
: entirely dark brown; eyes glabrous, brown; labial palpus with mixed brown and dark gray scales, porrect; antennae dark brown, nudum with 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBAC1C422FD2DE03B" box="[689,755,312,335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28</number>
segments (n= 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBBFBC422FC44E03B" box="[907,922,312,335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="4.0">4</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C442FCE5E01B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" box="[199,827,344,367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C442FECAE01B" box="[199,276,344,367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Thorax</emphasis>
: dorsally dark brown, ventrally brown; legs brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C462FCE0E35B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C462FEF0E0FB" box="[199,302,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Forewing</emphasis>
: male 
<quantity id="026F9B7A2A5C2C7FB9F1C462FDD3E0FB" box="[385,525,376,399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.475" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="24.75" valueMax="25.5" valueMin="24.0">24–25.5 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus id="1A2C883D2A5C2C7FBA51C462FD58E0FB" box="[545,646,376,399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="026F9B7A2A5C2C7FBAE2C462FD38E0FB" box="[658,742,376,399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
), average length = 
<quantity id="026F9B7A2A5C2C7FBBB8C462FBC7E0FB" box="[968,1049,376,399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBC3EC462FB85E0FB" box="[1102,1115,376,399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
); female 
<quantity id="026F9B7A2A5C2C7FBCB9C462FAC4E0FB" box="[1225,1306,376,399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="26.0">26 mm</quantity>
(Allotype). 
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8E7C482FED8E0DB" box="[151,262,408,431]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Upperside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FB963C482FE46E0DB" box="[275,408,408,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[184,1410,260,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[178,1416,255,1928]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 1 – 4. T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 1 – 2. Male holotype, dorsal and ventral; 3 – 4. Female allotype, dorsal and ventral; 5 – 8. T. tosta Evans, 1953; 5 – 6. Male from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral; 7 – 8. Female from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FB939C482FE88E0DB" box="[329,342,408,431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FB9F9C482FE46E0DB" box="[393,408,408,431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
): ground color dark purple-brown; basal, discal and postdiscal bands dark brown extending from costa to anal margin; submarginal area lighter than ground color; no costal fold. Female as in male, but lighter and with bands more evident. 
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB909C4C2FE36E09B" box="[377,488,472,495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Underside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FB987C4C2FD5AE09B" box="[503,644,472,495]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[184,1410,260,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[178,1416,255,1928]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 1 – 4. T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 1 – 2. Male holotype, dorsal and ventral; 3 – 4. Female allotype, dorsal and ventral; 5 – 8. T. tosta Evans, 1953; 5 – 6. Male from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral; 7 – 8. Female from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBA5FC4C2FDE2E09B" box="[559,572,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBA03C4C2FD5AE09B" box="[627,644,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
): ground color dark brown, paler distally; pale brown speculum covering about one-half from anterior portion of discal cell to anal margin and extending until two-thirds to tornus with a tuft of dark long hair-like scales originating from the base of the wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C722FD1FE3FB" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C722FEE8E33B" box="[199,310,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FB8B7C722FF22E33B" box="[199,252,568,591]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing
</emphasis>
: costa modified, resembling a hump that covers the forewing speculum. 
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FBC4AC722FB77E33B" box="[1082,1193,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Upperside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FBCC6C722FAE5E33B" box="[1206,1339,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[184,1410,260,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[178,1416,255,1928]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 1 – 4. T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 1 – 2. Male holotype, dorsal and ventral; 3 – 4. Female allotype, dorsal and ventral; 5 – 8. T. tosta Evans, 1953; 5 – 6. Male from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral; 7 – 8. Female from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBC9CC722FB27E33B" box="[1260,1273,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBD5CC722FAE5E33B" box="[1324,1339,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
): ground color dark purple-brown. 
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB9D8C742FDC9E31B" box="[424,535,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Underside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FBA55C742FD75E31B" box="[549,683,600,623]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[184,1410,260,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[178,1416,255,1928]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 1 – 4. T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 1 – 2. Male holotype, dorsal and ventral; 3 – 4. Female allotype, dorsal and ventral; 5 – 8. T. tosta Evans, 1953; 5 – 6. Male from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral; 7 – 8. Female from Santa Luzia, Maranhão, Brazil, dorsal and ventral. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBA2BC742FDB6E31B" box="[603,616,600,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBAEBC742FD75E31B" box="[667,683,600,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
): ground color dark brown; discal and postdiscal bands darker. Female as in male, but lighter and with bands more evident.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C782FB8EE3DB" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" box="[199,1104,664,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C782FEF2E3DB" box="[199,300,664,687]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Abdomen</emphasis>
: dorsally dark brown, ventrally brown. Female with no gland at 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBBACC782FC36E3DB" box="[988,1000,664,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="7.0">7</number>
th tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C7A2FC14E25B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C7A2FEB7E3BB" box="[199,361,696,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FB90DC7A2FE2DE3BB" box="[381,499,696,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,191,1095]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1429,191,1095]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 22. Genitalia of species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 9 – 13. Male genitalia of T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 9. lateral; 10 – 11. aedeagus, dorsal and lateral; 12. uncus and tegumen, dorsal. 13. right valva, internal view. 14 – 18. Male genitalia of T. tosta Evans, 1953; 14. lateral; 15 – 16. aedeagus, dorsal and lateral; 17. uncus and tegumen, dorsal. 18. right valva, internal view. 19 – 20. Female genitalia of T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 19. lateral; 20. ventral view of stergima. 21 – 22. Female genitalia of T. tosta Evans, 1953; 21. lateral; 22. ventral view of sterigma. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236396/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FB9C9C7A2FE2DE3BB" box="[441,499,696,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13</number>
</figureCitation>
): uncus triangular dorsally, curved ventrally, with two dorsal projections; tegumen squared dorsally; valva squared, ampulla separate from harpe and highly modified in a process with the distal portion dilated and serrated, harpe with a spine-like process curved inwards; aedeagus cylindrical, coecum thin and slightly bilobed, a group of small spines at the distal end of aedeagus, cornuti absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C622FB18E2FB" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C622FEA2E23B" box="[199,380,824,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5DAC2A1A2A5C2C7FB9F9C622FDD8E23B" box="[393,518,824,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,191,1095]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1429,191,1095]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 22. Genitalia of species of Tosta Evans, 1953. 9 – 13. Male genitalia of T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 9. lateral; 10 – 11. aedeagus, dorsal and lateral; 12. uncus and tegumen, dorsal. 13. right valva, internal view. 14 – 18. Male genitalia of T. tosta Evans, 1953; 14. lateral; 15 – 16. aedeagus, dorsal and lateral; 17. uncus and tegumen, dorsal. 18. right valva, internal view. 19 – 20. Female genitalia of T. pseudospeculum sp. nov.; 19. lateral; 20. ventral view of stergima. 21 – 22. Female genitalia of T. tosta Evans, 1953; 21. lateral; 22. ventral view of sterigma. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236396/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FB9CFC622FDD8E23B" box="[447,518,824,847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20</number>
</figureCitation>
): eighth tergite rectangular; papilla analis with postapophysis about the same length as the ductus bursae; sterigma formed by a a lamella antevaginalis with two well sclerotized projections extending laterally and by a broad and rectangular lamella postvaginalis; ductus and corpus bursae totally membranous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D8D65142A5C2C7FB8B7C682FCC0E2BB" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C682FCC0E2BB" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C682FE99E2DB" bold="true" box="[199,327,920,943]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the superficially similarity with 
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FBC7CC682FB3AE2DB" box="[1036,1252,920,943]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Speculum speculum</emphasis>
Austin, 
<number id="735F24B82A5C2C7FBD39C682FA5FE2DB" box="[1353,1409,920,943]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" value="1998.0">1998</number>
, a recently described genus and species from Rondônia, 
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FBAA5C6A2FCC4E2BB" box="[725,794,952,975]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D8D65142A5C2C7FB8B7C6C2FB0AE57B" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C528369F2A5C2C7FB8B7C6C2FB0AE57B" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="F7E3EA8D2A5C2C7FB8B7C6C2FE87E29B" bold="true" box="[199,345,984,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is currently known from Maranhão and Roraima states, 
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FBC4AC6C2FBA0E29B" box="[1082,1150,984,1007]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but it should also occur in other areas of the Amazon, such as Pará and Amazonas states, 
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FBB44C6E2FC54E57B" box="[820,906,1016,1039]" name="Guyana" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FBBE5C6E2FC25E57B" box="[917,1019,1016,1039]" name="Suriname" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Suriname</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BD80760F2A5C2C7FBC5EC6E2FB0EE57B" box="[1070,1232,1016,1039]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
